.TH "GNB" "1" "Apr 2026" "ganbatte" "ganbatte Manual"

.SH NAME
gnb-suggest - Suggest aliases and workflows from shell history


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgnb suggest [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Analyze shell history to suggest frequently used commands as aliases
and repeated command sequences as workflows.

.PP
ganbatte learns passively when eval "$(gnb shell-init)" is active. Once
enough commands are collected, suggest uses that data instead of raw shell
history for better accuracy.

.PP
Example:
  gnb suggest
  gnb suggest --apply
  gnb suggest --from-history   # force shell history source


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--apply\fP[=false]
	Apply suggested aliases and workflows to config

.PP
\fB--from-history\fP[=false]
	Force shell history source instead of track log

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for suggest

.PP
\fB--min-frequency\fP=5
	Minimum command frequency for alias suggestion

.PP
\fB--min-sequence\fP=3
	Minimum sequence frequency for workflow suggestion


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgnb(1)\fP


